---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { AUTHOR } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description={`About ${AUTHOR.name}`}>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <img
    src="/images/aslisho.jpg"
    alt={`Portrait of ${AUTHOR.name}`}
    width="160"
    height="160"
    class="portrait"
  />

  <p>
    I am <strong>{AUTHOR.name}</strong>, Research Associate at
    <a href="https://www.iis.ac.uk/">{AUTHOR.affiliation}</a>. I am a historian
    of the Middle East and North Africa with a strong interest in Central Asian
    and Persianate studies and cultures.
  </p>

  <p>
    I studied Arabic philology at Khorog State University in Tajikistan and 
	graduated with a Specialist Diploma in Oriental Studies.
    I hold an MPhil in Oriental Studies from the University of Oxford
    (2012–2014; Islamic studies and history, Arabic and Ottoman Turkish), and a
    PhD in Middle Eastern Studies from the University of Cambridge (2015–2019),
    with a thesis entitled
    <em>
      Traditions of Learning in Fāṭimid Ifrīqiya (296–362/909–973): Networks,
      Practices, and Institutions
    </em>.
  </p>

  <p>
    Then I worked as a postdoctoral research fellow at the ERC-funded
    <a href="https://kitab-project.org/">KITAB Project</a> (Aga Khan
    University), my primary area of research was the Islamic West — the
    Maghrib, al-Andalus, and Sicily — alongside contributions to the
    <a href="https://openiti.org/">OpenITI corpus</a>. My research interests
    include the Fatimid empire and the wider Islamicate world, premodern
    education and knowledge practices, connectivity, book culture, and
    computational approaches to Arabic and Persian textual traditions.
  </p>

  <p>
    I work with English, Arabic, Persian, Turkish, Russian, Italian, and
    French.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Email: <a href={`mailto:${AUTHOR.email}`}>{AUTHOR.email}</a><br />
    X / Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/fatimid_studies">@fatimid_studies</a>
    (academic) · <a href="https://twitter.com/aslishahqurbani">@aslishahqurbani</a>
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Anything published on this site is experimental and mostly intended for
    sharing preliminary research ideas.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .portrait {
    float: right;
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .portrait {
      float: none;
      display: block;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
